A: The problem is in this line:
File dir = new File(path + "\nameFolder");

You are trying to concatenate a string with a variable, but you are missing a + between the path and "\nameFolder". It should be:
File dir = new File(path + "/" + nameFolder);

Also, you should use mkdirs() instead of mkdir() because mkdir() only creates the directory if it does not exist, but mkdirs() creates the directory and any necessary parent directories.
So, your corrected code would be:
public void makeDirectory(String path, String nameFolder) {
    File dir = new File(path + "/" + nameFolder);
    dir.mkdirs();
}

This code will create the directory at the specified path if it does not exist. If the parent directories do not exist, they will also be created.

A: You are using the wrong slash in your File path. Use forward slash (/) instead of backslash (\).
public void makeDirectory(String path, String nameFolder) {
    File dir = new File(path + "/" + nameFolder);
    dir.mkdirs();
}


